Package: cuasmR
Type: Package
Title: R-Native SASS Disassembler and Patcher for NVIDIA sm_8x cubins
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R:
    person("Philipp", "Thoss", , "ph.thoss@gmx.de", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-4672-2792"))
Description: Read NVIDIA cubin files emitted by nvcc (CUDA 12.x and 13.x),
    decode their per-kernel SASS instructions via nvdisasm, allow byte-level
    edits of instruction or control-code words, and write a patched cubin.
    Targets the sm_8x (Ampere) family. Supersedes the upstream Python
    'CuAssembler' for our hand-edit workflow; tracks nvdisasm output rather
    than internal cubin layout, so it survives CUDA major-version bumps.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends: R (>= 4.0)
SystemRequirements: NVIDIA CUDA Toolkit 12.x or 13.x (nvdisasm on PATH)
Suggests: testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
